---
import "../styles/global.css";

import KFHeader from "../components/KFHeader.astro";
import KFMascot from "../components/KFMascot.astro";
import KFNavigation from "../components/KFNavigation.astro";
import KFSidebar from "../components/KFSidebar.astro";
import KFMoonPhase from "../components/net/KFMoonPhase.astro";
import KFNerdStats from "../components/net/KFNerdStats.astro";
import KFWebButtons from "../components/net/KFWebButtons.astro";
import KFBuildInfo from "../components/core/KFBuildInfo.astro";
import KFMusicPlayer from "../components/core/KFMusicPlayer.astro";

const title = "about";
const description = "about me.";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <KFHeader title={title} description={description} />
  </head>

  <body>
    <KFNavigation />

    <div class="website-grid">
      <div id="content" class="window">
        <div class="window-title">
          <p>{title}</p>
        </div>

        <div class="window-content">
          <div class="grid-justify">
            <div>
              <!-- biography -->
              <h2 class="edgy" style="margin: 0">biography</h2>
              <div class="window">
                <div
                  class="window-content"
                  style="display: flex; padding-bottom: 0;"
                >
                  <a
                    href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DLkNQgh4Ons"
                    style="margin: 0;padding: 0;"
                  >
                    <img
                      style="display: inline"
                      src="/imgs/misc/mekurume.png"
                      height="110px"
                    />
                  </a>
                  <p style="margin-left: 10px; margin-top: 0;">
                    Wow, look who decided to show up, -is what I would say, but
                    I doubt anyone would read this. Anyways, you can call me <i
                      >Junko</i
                    >, I'm the one who made this website. I'm currently a
                    student that's been making whatever I feel like making. I'm
                    not really good at anything, but I'm trying my best to
                    improve.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    Also, Isn't it funny that you can just be anyone on the internet?
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="window-content" style="margin: 0">
                  I’ve been programming since I was a child - probably not the
                  healthiest hobby growing up, but hey, here I am years later,
                  still doing it. Back then, I spent most of my time making
                  absolutely awful games in
                  <a href="https://www.clickteam.com/clickteam-fusion-2-5"
                    >Clickteam Fusion</a
                  >. Eventually, I moved on to <a href="https://wordpress.com/"
                    >WordPress</a
                  >, where my proudest creation was a clone of osu!'s
                  <a href="https://circle-people.com/skins/">Circle People</a> skins
                  website. I don’t have it anymore (and honestly, that might be for
                  the best), but it was fun while it lasted.
                  <br /><br />
                  Sometime around late 2018, I started learning
                  <a href="https://www.python.org/">Python</a> - mainly because I
                  wanted to make my own version of the osu! <a
                    href="https://top.gg/bot/289066747443675143">owo</a
                  > bot. If you can’t tell by now, I have a habit of making clones
                  of things I like. It’s honestly one of the best ways to learn, <i
                    >I think</i
                  >.
                  <br /><br />
                  Here are some quick facts about me:
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      I'm a big fan of Rhythm Games, here are some that I played
                      quite frequently:
                    </li>
                    <ul>
                      <li>maimai DX</li>
                      <li>CHUNITHM</li>
                      <li>Project Sekai</li>
                      <li>osu!</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>
                      My favourite Voice Synth is <a
                        href="https://www.youtube.com/@virtual_kaf">KAF</a
                      >, if you can't tell already from the website.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      I also like listening to Music, recently I've been
                      listening to <a
                        href="https://www.youtube.com/@tsumiki_NOMELONNOLEMON"
                        >[NOMELON NOLEMON]</a
                      >, especially the <a
                        href="https://www.last.fm/music/NOMELON+NOLEMON/%E3%83%AB%E3%83%BC%E3%83%AB"
                        >ルール</a
                      > album!
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- projects -->
              <br />
              <h2 class="edgy" style="margin: 0">projects</h2>
              <div class="window">
                <div class="window-content">
                  Listed below are my projects that I think are worth sharing...

                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <a href="https://github.com/xjunko/flower-rs">
                        flower-rs</a
                      > - an experimental unix-like kernel written in Rust.
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <a href="https://github.com/xjunko/moete-rs"> moete-rs</a> -
                      a community discord bot, mostly used for custom global emotes
                      and utilities, it is my most longest running project.
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <a href="https://github.com/xjunko/kurarin"> kurarin</a> - a
                      from scratch implementation of the osu!standard gamemode, written
                      in an experimental language, <a href="https://vlang.io/"
                        >V</a
                      >; fully supports .osu and .osr replay file format!
                    </li>
                  </ul>

                  <hr />
                  I think that should be enough to show what kind of projects I usually
                  work on, if you want to see more of my projects, you can check out
                  my <a href="https://github.com/xjunko">GitHub</a>!
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- contact -->
              <br />
              <h2 class="edgy" style="margin: 0">contact</h2>
              <div class="window">
                <div class="window-content">
                  I don't really use social media that much, so expect a delay
                  in my response. <br />
                  I'm on these platforms:
                  <ul class="list-no-space" style="padding-top: 5px;">
                    <li>discord - rmhakurei</li>
                    <li>
                      last.fm - <a href="https://www.last.fm/user/FireRedz"
                        >here</a
                      >
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      github - <a href="https://github.com/xjunko">xjunko</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>email - phony (at) kafu (dot) ovh</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- neighbours and other stuff -->
              <br />
              <div class="grid">
                <div class="border">
                  <h2 class="edgy" style="margin: 0">neighbours</h2>
                  <div class="window-content" style="text-align: center;">
                    <KFWebButtons />
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border">
                  <div class="window-content">
                    <a href="https://dokodemo.neocities.org/">
                      <img
                        style="width: 100%"
                        src="https://dokodemo.neocities.org/gamelounge/pokepi/suzuki.png"
                      />
                    </a>
                    <a
                      href="https://www.theotaku.com/quizzes/view/2019/what_okami_character_are_you%3F"
                    >
                      <img
                        style="width: 100%"
                        src="http://www.theotaku.com/guru_results/2019_Waka.jpg"
                        alt="What Okami Character Are You?"
                      />
                      <br />
                    </a>
                    <div
                      style="display: flex;align-items: center;justify-content: center;gap: 5px;"
                    >
                      <KFMoonPhase />
                      <KFNerdStats />
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- website info -->
              <br />
              <h2 class="edgy" style="margin: 0">built with</h2>
              <div class="window">
                <div class="window-content">
                  <p>
                    <p>
                      This website were made using <a
                        href="https://vscodium.com/">VSCodium</a
                      >, using <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a>; source
                      code is available
                      <a href="https://github.com/xjunko/home">[here]</a>.
                      <br />
                      <KFBuildInfo />
                    </p>
                    <h3 id="fonts">fonts</h3>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
                        <a
                          href="https://github.com/TakWolf/ark-pixel-font/releases"
                          >Ark Pixel</a
                        > by <a href="https://github.com/TakWolf">@TakWolf</a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <a
                          href="https://www.myfonts.com/pages/linotype-neue-haas-grotesk"
                          >Neue Haas Grotesk</a
                        > by Linotype
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <a href="https://terminus-font.sourceforge.net/"
                          >Terminus</a
                        > by Kevin Dresser (?)
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                    <h3 id="arts">arts</h3>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
                        <a href="https://cevio.fandom.com/wiki/KAFU"
                          >Header Kafu</a
                        > by PALOW.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <a href="https://www.pixiv.net/en/artworks/117194838"
                          >Home Kafu</a
                        > by <a href="https://www.pixiv.net/en/users/93735034"
                          >落島</a
                        >
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <a href="https://dowman-s.tumblr.com/post/145993340985"
                          >Ononoki Index</a
                        > by <a href="https://dowman-s.tumblr.com/">dowman-s</a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Araragi, Nadeko, Manga cover from the <a
                          href="https://mangadex.org/title/4265c437-7d57-4d31-9b1d-0e574a07b7b7/bakemonogatari"
                          >Monogatari series</a
                        >
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div id="sidebar">
        <KFSidebar isHomePage={true} />
      </div>
    </div>

    <KFMascot mascot="cover" />
    <KFMusicPlayer />
  </body>
</html>
